properties.sfomuseum:description: Handwritten letter from Harold M. Bixby to his wife, Debby Bixby, dated June 8, [1936], on stationery from the Manila Hotel; includes description of plans to travel to New York on the Clipper, report that the Hawaii Clipper is having a hull leak repaired in Cavite per [Captain R.O.D.] Sullivan, brief description of political situation in China; mentions [William L.] Bond, Webber and Fisk (Clipper personnel); original document missing pages.
